com.ti.debug.engine.scripting

Class Symbol

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ti.debug.engine.scripting.Symbol

  • public class Symbol
extends java.lang.Object
    This class encapsulates the symbol methods. An instance of this class is automatically created when a new session is opened.

    Note: When specifying file paths during function calls, the slashes need to be represented using '/' or '\\' (with an escape character).

    Note2: This class cannot be used for looking up registered variables. To read and write to registered variables, use the following:
    debugSession.expression.evaluate( "i" ); // returns the value of i
    debugSession.expression.evaluate( "i = 7" ); // sets the value of i to 7

    // Create Environment and open a debug session
    ScriptingEnvironment env = new ScriptingEnvironment();
    DebugServer myServer = (DebugServer) env.getServer("DebugServer.1");
    DebugSession mySession = myServer.openSession("*", "*");

    ...

    // Get the address of a symbol
    String sMain = mySession.symbol.getAddress("main");
    String sMyFunc = mySession.symbol.getAddress("_myfunc");

      • add

        public void add(java.lang.String fileName)
         throws ScriptingException
        Add all of the symbols from the given file to the debugger's symbol manager. Any existing symbols on the target will remain loaded and these symbols will be appended to them
        Parameters:
        fileName - (String) the name of the file to add symbols for. Relative paths are permitted, use ScripingEnvironment.setCurrentDirectory(String) to change the current working directory.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • addWithOffset

        public void addWithOffset(java.lang.String fileName,
                          long codeStart,
                          long dataStart)
                   throws ScriptingException
        Adds the specified program's symbols into the debugger's symbol manager. Any existing symbols on the target will remain loaded and these symbols will be appended to them. Symbols associated with the program's code sections will be added starting at codeStart while the program's data sections will be added starting at dataStart.
        Parameters:
        fileName - (String) the name of the file to add symbols for. Relative paths are permitted, use ScripingEnvironment.setCurrentDirectory(String) to change the current working directory.
        codeStart - (long) the starting address to start adding the program's symbols
        dataStart - (long) the starting address to start adding the data's symbols
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • addWithRelativeOffset

        public void addWithRelativeOffset(java.lang.String fileName,
                                  long codeOffset,
                                  long dataOffset)
                           throws ScriptingException
        Adds the specified program's symbols into the debugger's symbol manager. Any existing symbols on the target will remain loaded and these symbols will be appended to them. Symbols associated with the program's code sections will be moved by codeOffset while the program's data sections will be moved by dataOffset.
        Parameters:
        fileName - (String) the name of the file to add symbols for. Relative paths are permitted, use ScripingEnvironment.setCurrentDirectory(String) to change the current working directory.
        codeOffset - (long) the offset to move the program's code section
        dataOffset - (long) the offset to move the program's data section
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

      • exists

        public boolean exists(java.lang.String sSymbol)
               throws ScriptingException
        Check whether a specified symbol exists or not.

        Note: Types Definitions (structs, classes, etc.) are valid symbols - but have no address on the target - so this method will return false.
        Parameters:
        sSymbol - name of the symbol.
        Returns:
        true if the specified symbol exists, false if is does not.
        Throws:
        ScriptingException

                           long dataStart)

        Loads the specified program's symbols into the debugger's symbol manager. Any existing symbols on the target will be unloaded. Symbols associated with the program's code sections will be added starting at codeStart while the program's data sections will be added starting at dataStart.

        codeStart - (long) the starting address to start adding the program's symbols
        dataStart - (long) the starting address to start adding the data's symbols

      • lookupSymbol

        public java.lang.String lookupSymbol(int nPage,
                                     long nAddress)
        Lookup the symbol found at a specified address. Note: If multiple symbols exist at the same address (i.e. "abort", "C$$EXIT") we cannot guarantee which one will be returned.
        Parameters:
        nPage - memory page
        nAddress - address to lookup a symbol
        Returns:
        The name of symbol found at the specified address, or an empty string ("") if no symbol is found at that address.

      • lookupSymbols

        public java.lang.String[] lookupSymbols(int nPage,
                                        long nAddress)
        Lookup all of the symbols found at a specified address and return them in an array.
        Parameters:
        nPage - memory page
        nAddress - address to lookup a symbol
        Returns:
        An array of Strings containing all of the symbol found at the specified address, or an empty array if no symbols were found.
